title: Winter  is Wonderful

title: A Foggy Night

text: the land of neglect i dreamt of a place where the air is clean,                                                                            the grass is green,  the sky is                                                                             blue and the water is crystal clear.  it                                                                                 is our planet,  the earth.  i opened                                                                           my eyes but i donâ’t see what i dreamt.                                                                            i see contaminated water,  a smoggy sky                                                                             and withered grass.  i smelt toxic smoke,  car                                     emissions and factory smoke  lingering                                                                                                                                                          in the air.  i heard rumbling noises from                                                                                                                                                              the passing trucks and sound pounded                                                                    on my ears.  i still feel awful because                                                                      i contributed to this mess.

title: Lonely

text: crunch,  swish, hey,  pang.  these are the sounds that surrond me.  here i sit,  forgotten, unnoticed.  i eat my lunch while chatter and laughter flow around me,  as if i dont exist.   and sometimes i wonder if i do exist.  what's wrong with me? why me? why? why? questions and doubts fil my head,  i can think of nothing else.   i am unaccepted and unwanted.  friends seem a distint memory.   ring!!  the bell sounds and my daily torture is over.  i slip past people,  on to my next class.  will i ever belong? i'm not sure but i think i'll paste on a smile and go say ''hi'' to that girl over there.   that's a start,  right?

title: Things Will Never Be The Same
author: amber
text: things will never be the same since that dreary july day i'm looking back on those things you told me and the things that you wouldn't say  you tell me you're ok but i know that you're not your clothes are a mess and your eyes are blood shot you carry rocks on your back that are weighing you down  putting on emotional weight and twisting your face into a  frown we both know that you made a mistake  they're lucky, those lives that you didn't take  it could have been worse don't you see?  you may have lost a lot of things but you haven't lost me.   so think of the sunshine instead of the rain think of the happiness instead of the pain.   i forgive you isn't that enough?  i always do when times get rough  that thing you did,  it was a terrible thing to do  but you need to know that i'm always here for you.

title: A Lost Treasure
author: amelia
text: peace is swinging on a hammock  in the cool summer breeze,   when you can just let out all of your troubles,  set them free.  peace is seeing lilies dancing in the sun,  reminding you how life is short,  and you should go have fun.  peace is watching the young grow up,  like watching a flower blooming for the first time,  like going up a tree,  just to have yourself a good climb.  peace is a blessing,  that only some of us can keep.  peace should be cherished,  like a good nights sleep.  unfortunately,  there's not enough to go around.  so any peace that you have,  is like a lost treasure being found.

title: My pet
author: amna
text: one day for an hour or so i glanced and glanced. . .  but didn't realize,  it was a friend or foe,  a beautiful shape; in-front of me it was placed,  it whined and barked and kept on doing so and once again i glanced and glanced. . .  and kept on doing so until he came to me and bowed.   he wagged his tail and lept high and circled me twice. . . no thrice! i crouched and felt his silky coat which was rough but felt me silk,  why it happened no-one knows.   i patted him and he barked i held him and strolled along; everyone glanced and glanced. . .  but it pleased me as i was not very long.  i took him home and looked for the couch in which he was to be placed.  i played and played with him all day long,  and i was quite amazed because he barked and barked all day long.   and now it has been two years from then,  he and i have become friends forever.  he barks and barks all day long and leaves me quite amazed,  i just glance and glance and keep on doing so.

title: Summer Sadness
author: amy
text: you'd think i'd be happy  now that school is out.   you'd think i'd want to run and play.   jump up and scream and shout.   but that's not how i feel today.   i feel sad and alone  i miss my friends that i had at school  you can sense it in my tone.   i miss the way we used to laugh  at things that seemed so dumb  and when we got in trouble  our heads would feel so numb  but when that was all over  when all the fun was lost  i couldn't feel the laughter  all i felt was the frost  the frost of bitter loneliness  the coldness of my mind  memories, oh, the memories  are all that i can find.   i sit here and i think  about all we've said and done  all the arguements and complaints  oh we had a ton  but we were always friends through the thick and thin  and now i know  our friendship will never end

title: The Real Wanderer

title: Literature
author: amy
text: how is it i can print my very soul onto something so temporary as this,  the paper feels nothing but the pencil's kiss.  and to put it in such worldly terms,  when what i feel is so eternal,  so everlasting,  even after i said it was past me.  i picked myself up after i fell,   but within my entity it continues to dwell.  my soul may be drowning in the depths of despair,  and the rest of the world doesn't seem to care,  but the i use phraseology as my transient bliss,  and i know that nothing can take away this.  it's never perpetual,  but it's all i got,  i spit out the parlance without a second thought.  it's my soothing remedy in a world of pain,  when all people seem to do is play some stupid game.  i'll stand tall even if it means standing alone.  i'll walk the path i choose not one i'm shown.  amy whitaker

title: What Being Bullied Feels Like
author: analisia
text: being bullied feels like a bowling ball getting chucked at your head.  when you get bullied a dark cloud goes over you and you feel abandoned.  you hide yourself in the shadows so no one can see you crying.  you become unable to concentrate in class causing grades to drop.  you become afraid to step foot in school because you know the bully will be there.  you realize words hurt just as much as being physically bullied.  when you hear them call you words like â“worthlessâ” and â“uglyâ” you want to run and cry.  you become afraid to check texts,  emails,  or social media.  you start to pretend you're ok when you know youâ’re not,  you wear a fake smile.  your hardest trying is never good enough for the bully and you no longer know what to do.  you eat lunch alone by the trashcan on the ground because you can't be accepted.  you become broken just wishing you could be the same person you used to be.  when the bully comes near you,  you tense up and wish you could be invisible.  you become insecure and don't want to ever be seen again.  you begin to get emotionally destroyed and you slowly fade away.  when something is said about you,  you completely change yourself to try and be what they want you to be.  you begin to think its your fault and you start hating yourself for it.  you just wish you had someone that understood,  someone to talk to.  you start to cry yourself to sleep and you feel unwanted by everyone.  you start to skip meals and tell yourself you're not worth it.

title: Metaphor life
author: anna
text: running at half speed down an endless cave.  about to turn a corner  i see a light.  i feel cold water surrounding my sneakers giving me the chills.  i look down at them for the longest time.  after a while the water seeps into the ground.  the light is getting brighter now.  its blinding, so blinding that i can't find my way then the light starts to dim.  a moment of silence.  i can feel the water starting to rise again a loud rumble fills the air i look around for an explanation then i look forward and see water flowing through the cracks in the walls the water is up to my neck i feel so scared! will i be able to survive?

title: I Have Hope: A Tribute to the Holocaust
author: anna
text: the gleam of their ghastly front teeth  their muzzles furiously black like coal glinting in the darkened ghetto threatening to sink razors into my flesh threatening to smash my beaten carcass onto rugged concrete yet holding on waiting for their master's ferocity and anger to will them into murder for they are just creatures of the earth  one thin tail sweeps into a feeble upward motion.   crammed into a freight train seventy six people crowd my soul wall-to-wall in one rusted,  beaten car the only exit is small and barred a window far from my reach despair,  darkness,  desolation my father will never see me again i shall resolve myself to observe the patterns hidden in the rust of this horrid,  hateful car my journey lurches forward  with a sudden puff of smoke suddenly,  i do not have hate for this single train car it is simply a welded metal slab  i found a jewish star etched in the rust  the hair is ripped from my head shorn with a metal blade sliced like a cut of meat shaming my flaking scalp ss man's yellow eyes cut  deep into my thoughts and my mind i am afraid he can hear the words inside me as i work for twelve hours with no rest driven to the time where raw wounds and aching muscles vanish into numbness  and vanish into the sod that i dig shattering it with ripe,  red blood and yet i find comfort in my work here  for work will make me free  in the rain today hungarian children trembled  outside a gas chamber their bodies were ghosts mingling with drops of silver rain and yet the tears that fell from their eyes  beckoned to me as clear as the sun  the naked gypsy girls sunken eyes pleading with me from the back of a wagon where they were loaded their wilted,  dead limbs entwining like tree branches providing comfort to their souls  already rejoicing in heaven  the crematories smoke day and night their open chimneys breathe gray fury into my barrack for those who have died here want revenge justice freedom yet those people can do not a thing they have already passed into nothing  but their souls are free  my journey is fading into darkness eyes sink further into their sockets face is pale and gaunt back is raw from lashings poundings thrashings tiredness is no longer a feeling instead it is a way of life i know the time is drawing near gas chambers are closer than the ground beneath my feet sickness is clutching at my lungs skinny fingers inch up my neck to strangle me for eternity  but i shall live on  last night,  i was torn ripped from my home at midnight pulled by the fraying collar of my  only shirt down to the gas chambers slapped into line shoved into place i was just a playing piece in hitler's war a powerless girl an unimportant child marked only with a jewish star finally i cried who would watch my tears? who would pity my  oncoming death? i was alone dying to hate prejudice anger then i heard a voice shivering in the darkness nothing more than a quiver yet a symphony to me â“where are you? i know you are here!â” my best friend forever and ever tears jolt to a halt suddenly i look into a  star-filled sky my name is called for gassing â“come  â“now!â” a bellow crashing like angry timpani  being wailed upon with drummer's mallets yet i know inside me though i will die  i will never again be alone

title: The Gift of Friendship
author: annie

title: The Last Day of School
author: annie
text: they're all waiting for the end.  but they're still stuck in school.  most of their friends decided that they will go to the pool.    but little maddie sits alone,  for she would be very late.  she had a doctor's checkup,  and wanted her friends to wait.    the school bell rings,  they run outdoors but maddie stays inside her mom comes to pick her up and her sad feelings she will hide.    after her appointment,  maddie still feels very sad.  her mom drops her off at the pool,  but then she feels suddenly glad.    her shy,  good friend jimmy is at the entrance,  standing there.  all maddie's friends are behind him,  and for once,  maddie knows they care.

title: I Remember the Time of the Holocaust
author: annika
text: i remember when life was normal  i remember when our religion did not matter  i remember when we could go wherever we wanted to  and now those times have gone away.   i remember when i could fly free like a butterfly in the open blue sky  i remember when we did not have to have a yellow star pined to all of our clothing  i remember when we were not surrounded with bombs exploding and voices as loud as the angry waves crashing into the rocks at the ocean shore  even now i still have hope that sometime this dreadful time will be over and life will be normal again  i remember waking up every morning and wondering if i would ever wake up again  but i hope one day when i wake up that i will be free.

title: Betrayal
author: annmarie
text: they almost had me,  they almost got the real me.  i never could be me for real.  i always wore a mask,  a costume to hide the real me.  just as the costume was coming off it happened,  like a train wreck it happened.  like the twin towers i fell,  fell 20 stories from my heart.  i smashed like an egg falling off the ledge.  i broke like an old gold locket.  like a tattered shirt i unraveled.  my blank canvas is now black.  like humpty dumpty i fell and no one could put me back together again.  in a way they were wearing a mask too,  pretending to be my friends.  unlike me their mask came off.  if i left would anyone miss me? if i left would they write? if i cried would they care? my life is like a bad story with no ending.  i'm the star that's gone dull.  i was forgotten like yesterdays newspaper head line,  old and unimportant.  they betrayed me.

title: I Know  A Girl
author: ariel
text: i know a girl who carries the weight of the world on her shoulders,  she has many problems to face a day.   i know a girl,  who tends to take on problems that arise becuase she wants a challenge,  and knows secretly that it will make her stronger.   i know a girl who is sad,  she's lost people in her life that mean a lot.   i know a girl who loves to read,  she loves to get into books.   i know a girl that loves to do new things,  even when people may say that they dislike them.   i know a girl who deals with other people's problems,  this girl wants to help her friends when they are down.   i know a girl who never will give up on her dream.    i know a girl,  this girl is myself.

title: Choices
author: ariel
text: no i don't know why,  why you care,  sometimes i think,  no one would even notice if i wasn't there,  i can't choose,  if you want me to like you,  or someone else wants me to like them too,  all i can do,  is look for signs,  and wonder if they mean you want me to like you.

title: No Going Back
author: ariel
text: i've got to take action,  i know it is wrong,  i see this girl cheating,  she's looking at me as if a plead not to tell,  i have to ignore her,  it's not right,  i have to go up and tell the teacher,  i know it's the right thing to do,  i finished my test,  so now that i am through,  i might as well go say this girl is cheating and get over with her annoying glares for the rest of school.

title: Number 19
author: ariel
text: i watch you from the football field,  your almost up to bat,  would you look at that? your friend just hit a home run,  i bet you'll do the same,  the thing i love the most,  is watching you play,  for you are very strong,  that goes without saying,  now,  i'd wish you'd just notice me,  like i notice you.

title: The Prom
author: ariel
text: my maskara's running onto my dress,  i look like a complete mess,  this is not how it should be,  i should be in his arms dancing happily,  but he has just set that apart,  my dream now differed,  all of the people staring at me,  while i'm off to the side,  thinking,  boy,  glad that isn't me,  i surely wouldn't want to be that unhappy,  crowds start to gather around,  your brown eyes gaze down at me,  an outstretched hand,  is placed infront of me,  i take it graciousley,  and dance the rest of the night away like i had imagined,  being happy.

title: A Message to my Friends
author: ariel
text: this is for all my friends,  no matter where they are,  i love you all,  and appreciate you so,  so keep on talking,  making jokes,  and sitting at the lunch table with me.   continue to share your fears and dreams,  those are interesting to hear,  tell me your problem,  and i'll try to help,  unless it has to do with computers,  then you'd really need help,  from someone else!  just please keep on doing the things that you do,  telling me the days events,  and the bad things too,  you know i'll always be there for you.

title: The Window
author: ariel
text: i look out the window,  what do i see? an ocean,  know what? it reminds me,  it reminds me of,  some path that's long and exciting,  maybe love? i'm not so sure,  whatever it is,  it seems to be like quite an adventure,  so i look out my window,  and you know what i see,  the sunset's fading away,  just as i go to sleep,  good night again,   till next time,  when i sit at my window looking over the ocean.

title: The Carnival
author: ariel
text: the star trooper! oh my! how much i love that ride! i can go on it again and again,  eleven times in a row,  or maybe just ten! that ride is the best,  just like the rest,  how i can't wait till the carnival.   my friends are a mess,  there's cotton candy on my face,  my friends are now laughing at me,  we go on the ferris wheel,  that's when i squeal,  no one shake that seat!  the carnival's so much fun,  whenever i hear it's in town,  i want to run to be first on line for buying the bracelet.

title: The Soldier's Final Cry
author: ariel
text: i have to say,  while fighting this battle day to day,  i miss my kids,  so many soldiers are dead.   i miss the october sky,  my wife used to make pumpkin pie,  oh,  how i long for some so!  day in,  and day out,  i hear the crys of men shouting their last words to one another.   i'm on the battlefeild,  and i shriek,  why,  why did i choose to fight for my country? soldiers hear my cry,  they come by me and mutter the words why,  oh why? just then a man from the opposite side,  layed down on the feild,  why,  oh why? was all he could cry.

title: My Reflection
author: ariel
text: yes i am a trouble maker,  always being yelled at,  no matter what,  i object,  is this what happens when you are a teenager?  i have pimples galore,  and when i'm embarassed my face goes beet red,  but that doesn't stop me from saying what needs to be said.   if i told you what's on my mind all the time,  would that make you happy? i take your critisism with a smile,  in the meanwhile,  i am frowning inside.   if i was just like every other student or person,  i would not be me,  and this world would be a boring place,  where no one is unique,  and all the emotions all the time would be the same.

title: Green
author: ariel
text: green is new grown grass in spring,  leaves on a new grown tree,  a snapple bottle cap.   green sounds relaxing,  like laughter of a best friend,  the breeze of a ocean in the carribbean.   green tastes sweet as taking a forkful of lemon meringue pie and placing it in one's mouth,  and  the taste of crisp air on an autumn day.   if green could do anything,  it would relax with a book in a meadow all day long,  and not have a care in the world.

title: Treasured Memories

title: The Bahamas
author: avery
text: the bahamas are a very exciting,  enjoyable,  ecstatic place to visit.  i love the bahamas because it is such a calm place.  the ocean says hello to us when we walk the beach.  blue skies all day and busy people rushing around.  so many people trying to advertise their merchandise.  tourists come from all over the world to see the beautiful landscape.  whoosh the waves roll up on high tide.  the birds are chirping with excitement for the new ships coming in.  honk! honk! the ships horn announce their new arrival.  the sand tickles my feet in my flip flops.  the fish in the ocean jump up so freely,  and flawlessly out of the water.  many boats roam the calm,  clear waters.  the sun beats down on our dark,  tanned skin.  palm trees sway in the light breeze.  wet swimsuits and towels line our hotel bathroom.

title: Stars
author: ayesha
text: stars are so wonderful wandering through the sky.   they are so big yet they appear so small that makes it more of a reason to like them  stars let people think about what is going on in their life  other things that they just don't have the time to think about.   kids beg their parents to let them watch the stars outside,   they somehow feel that their parents are watching too (the truth is they are) when looking at the stars you are totally focused.   nothing will distract you you will have the patience that you have never had before.  to look and feel something so special, so tender  that you have a feeling things will be better in your life but you're still focusing on the stars  all of this sounds so impossible,  yet it'so true if stars weren't here or they suddenly disappeared.   the little kids won't be happy or amazed.  adults wouldn't come out to enjoy their special bond between then  the sky would be an empty mass.   and there would be a hole left in my heart.

title: A Great Friendship
author: becca
text: as i walked along the shore the waves came in without a roar.  all by myself and all alone i sat down and began to moan.   for i knew that i was sick and really feared i might die quick! and it seemed like all my days had just flown by in a haze.   i was terribly scared and worried at that so dozing off i took a small nap.  when i awoke something had changed,  something was strange.   for now staring at me were two gentle blue eyes,  filled with tears and tiny cries.  it was my best friend steve who had always been there for me.   when he noticed i had woken up,  he quickly came over and picked me up.  then he whispered,  ''i know i never told you this,  but i've always loved you, '' then gave me a kiss.   right then and there,  i finally relized  how much our friendship really prized.  but then i began to cry,  knowing that i was going to die.   but then a voice came from the distance yelling with great brilliance,  ''we've found the cure!'' ''we've found the cure!''  at first i could not believe my ears for i thought it was something one mishears.  but what i was hearing truely was the answer,  they had finally found the cure for cancer!  i was one of the firsts to go through the operation.  when i was done,  the doctor said,  ''everythig is finally done. '' when i got out of the operating room,  there my best friend steve was waiting for me!

text: with a cutlass at my side,  iwill use it with pride,  you will never threaten me,  its the plank or my team.   im the badest of the bunch,  and i pack a strong punch,  black pearl is my mighty ship,  nothing can make it tip,   jack sparrow is my name,  raiding ships is my game,  i am never ever caught,  as my dad always taught.   my life is one big shamble,  its the life of gamble,  but first if you hear from me,  i'd never go to sea.

title: Wishes For Him
author: becky
text: i want him to comeback,  i want him to come home.  i want him to see how much his children have grown.  i want him to feel safe when he walks down the street.  i want him to say something that isn't discreet.  i want him to lay down and sleep in his own bed.  i want him to hear the first words his child said.   i want him to feel happy and not feel pain.  i want him to hear the sounds of a crane.  i want him to come home as soon as he can.  i want him to come home,  the exact same man.

title: Seasons
author: becky
text: summer is fun,  spring is too! winter is snowy,  which makes me blue.  autumn is like a piece of art.  which makes me never want to part.  i wish all the seasons would be the same,  so i wouldn't have to feel the shame.

title: Squirrel Chase

text: this squirrel scampers up and down the tree - he moves much too fast for me.  i try to catch him in the park,  but he quickly climbs a tree's soft bark.  when i spot him,  the speedy bloke,  he makes a getaway in a sturdy oak.  this time i'll catch him,  i think i'm able. . .  but if i blink he's up a maple.  he flashes me a look of pure evil; i've been ousmarted by a furry weasel!

title: Summer
author: benjamin
text: i love the summer stay up late wake up at two thirty in the afternoon then run around all day in the sun.   hot dogs,  burgers,  and barbecue sizzling and steaming on the grill you can smell it all over the neighborhood the tingling aroma causing you to stop what you are doing.   swimming,  running,  throwing a football,  kicking a soccer ball all of my favorite summer activities to do every summer day i love the summer!

title: I am great, I am great

title: The dog that died
author: benjamin
text: the dog was sweet,  he was oh so very small,  all the other dogs were very tall,  although he got picked on,  he was very brave,  until he got buried in the grave,  we all remember him,  in our hearts,  that sad old little bark.

title: Chocolate Milk
author: benjamin
text: after a game or a practice i think,  rich,  thick and chocolaty milk i like to drink.   it satisfies hunger and quenches my thirst.  i don't want chips or cookies,  i want it first.   so,  pour in the goodness,  extra chocolate please.  don't make me wait patiently,  for that is a tease.   i can't wait to have it.   my taste buds want more.  i'm out of the syrup; please go to the store!  it's delicious and tasty and it is smooth as silk.  and get me,  oh get me,  some more chocolate milk.

title: The Girl in the Forbidden Mirror
author: bethany
text: whos in the mirror who do i see? not a women in fashion magazine.  i see a girl in white,  and medium height why is she so sad why does she wear a frown she wants to be pretty she wants to stand out.  she realizes that the more she is depressed the sicker she'll get,  so she looks in the mirror,  tells herself shes pretty she looks in the mirror and says the girl. . . . in the mirror is me!!!

title: Friends
author: betsy
text: laugh like you've never laughed.  run,  feel like you two are the only ones.  talk,  because you know she'll listen.  tell secrets,  she wont tell even the juciest ones.  whisper,  because they will know you have a secret.  cry,  because your only human and she will give you a shoulder.  hug,  because sometimes you just need one.  sing to the radio,  like no one but her can here you.  love,  because of her.  smile,  because she is there.

title: Friends Remember You
author: betsy
text: friends remember you.  they will if you care.  smile at them even when your not happy.  hug them even though your not in the mood.  laugh with them even when it isnt funny.  listen to their secrets even when you dont care.  scream with them when they're happy even when there isnt anything to scream about.  let them chohose what to do even when it is boring.  don't tell them bad things about their crush.  and remember them.

title: Sandy
author: betsy
text: she wasnt just anyone.  she was my best friend.  she was always there to listen to my problems.  she could always make me smile. she was my only friend.  she never made fun of me,  or talked behind my back.  but now she is gone forever.  sandy wasnt just any bird she was mine.

text: heâ’s passionate  he knows whatâ’s right for me,    he knows what i want,    he knows what i like,    he knows what makes me laugh,    he knows what makes me mad,    he knows what makes me cry,    heâ’s thoughtful   he knows my birthday,    he knows my crabby days,    he knows my happy days,    he knows my weird days,    he is my one and only              dad!
